
# Quick Start n8n

Running n8n with npx (requires Node.js)
```
npx n8n
```

Or running with Docker
```
docker volume create n8n_data
docker run -it --rm --name n8n -p 5678:5678 -v n8n_data:/home/node/.n8n docker.n8n.io/n8nio/n8n
```

Editor available at http://localhost:5678

# Set up
Visual representation of workflows are included in their representative folders

1. Import Workflow
Load the three json files into three separate n8n instance.

2. Connect Credentials
For each workflow, click on the 'Google Gemini Chat Model' node and add in your API. Node is changable to other AI models if necessary.

3. Triggering Workflow (Requires running api.py and test.py files)
The workflows are triggered by hosting api.py and running test_api.py, test_api_ba.py, and test_api_combined.py for finance, sales, and the full business advisory analysis respectively.